With the rising costs of centerfire ammunition, the new Tactical .22 rimfires are meant for recreational shooters, as well as those searching for a cost-effective training platform, according to Mossberg.

EHUD APPENDIX CARRY HOLSTER (GLK 19/23/25/33 Rt hand) Black

Ehud was an Old Testament special operator that worked in a truly non-permissive environment.  He was able to get his weapon past very high level scrutiny to carry out his mission.  If he were alive today and carrying a modern pistol, he'd have it holstered in this rig.

This is an Inside the Waistband Appendix Holster.  It makes concealed carry very easy and yet is the fastest holster we have ever worked with.   

The Ehud Holster for Appendix Carry!!! A carefully designed A/C IWB holster with maximum concealment and comfort in mind, the Ehud is like no other of its type. The J-hook belt loops allow you to position your handgun just where you need it. This holster is made with a rearward cant for Appendix Carry but can be customized for any configuration; the butt of the weapon will sit approximately 3/4 " to 1" higher then the belt line depending on the weapon allowing a full index of the handgun.

NOTE ON HOLSTER LENGTH - The holsters all come in one standard length for a given pistol model.  So for example, a holster made for a Glock 17 will fit a Glock 19, and a Glock 26 as well.  If you order a Glock 26 holster, you will get the standard holster that fits all 9mm/40 cal Glocks, and not a short Glock 26 specific holster. title: For Sale:  12 Ga. Beretta 686 Onyx with Browning Case
location: North St. Petersburg, Tampa/St. Pete, Florida
postcontent:
a 686 Onyx shotgun.

26" OU Barrels
3" Magnum Chambers
Automatic Ejectors
First Barrel Selector on Safety
First shot inertia selector for second shot 


The first Onyx - as the name suggests - had completely black metalwork. The action is machined from a solid block of steel with no protrusions through the bottom of the action.  The barrels hinge into the action on stub pins or trunnions in each side of the action wall, and lock up is achieved by a U-bolt protruding through the action face. These engage in corresponding holes in the breech face of the barrels.  The action walls also have cut outs that the barrel fences engage with, thereby producing a very strong closure.

Woodwork is fairly plain yet functional with this gun. The wood has been treated to a thick gloss polyurethane type finish. The traditional-looking chequering is certainly machine cut but in spite of that the points and diamonds are very neatly cut. In fact they're extremely precise.  The stock is finished with a black rubber recoil pad of about 3/4in thickness, which feels comfortable and does help soften the recoil when heavier cartridges are used in the gun.

title: Want To Buy:  So you want to buy a suppressor?
postcontent:
If you can LEGALLY purchase a firearm, you may purchase a supressor.

Suppressors, like machine-guns, are regulated under the National Firearms Act (NFA) of 1934, and are regulated by the Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, and Firearms.

STEPS REQUIRED TO PURCHASE A SUPPRESSOR

1. The first step is to locate a Class 3 dealer.

2. The Class 3 dealer will provide the prospective purchaser with duplicate ATF Form 4's and two sets of fingerprint cards.

3. The Form 4's must be filled out on both sides, with passport photos of the prospective buyer affixed to the backside of the form.

4. The buyer then has the Chief Law Enforcement officer sign the rear of the Form 4's attesting the prospective purchaser does not possess a criminal record and is not wanted.

5. The two fingerprint cards must be completed and signed by a Law Enforcement agency.

6. The completed paperwork is then sent to the Department of the Treasury with a check or money order for $200.00. The $200.00 is known as a "transfer tax" because it must be paid whenever ownership of the silencer is "transferred" (in this case, the dealer to the prospective purchaser). As long as ownership remains with the same person, the tax need not be paid again. Only if the owner sells it will a new transfer tax need to be paid. An owner may will his suppressor to a lawful heir with no tax incurred.

7. Once the paperwork is submitted, it normally takes 60 to 120 days to receive the approved, stamped paperwork from the NFA Branch. It is only upon the return of the approved paperwork that the dealer can allow the prospective purchaser to take possession of their new suppressor.

8. A copy of the approved paperwork must accompany the suppressor at all times (the original should be stored in a safe deposit box).

9. Suppressors can be transported to other states that allow their ownership, but to transport a suppressor into one of the states which prohibit private ownership can subject the owner to serious state felony charges.

title: For Sale:  M4 Carbine, .223/5.56 16" W/Detachable Carry Handle, Telescoping Stock, Black Finish 30 Round Mag
postcontent:
One of our ALL TIME BEST Carbine models, the M4 Type features a distinctive Military Barrel Profile and Six Position Telestock – great for 3 Gun Match Shooting, Home Defense and Law Enforcement use.



The Bushmaster A2 & A3 Type Patrolman’s Carbines are modeled after our M4 Type Carbines, but with additional barrel length to make them legal for sale to individual officers (semi-automatic configuration with 16" barrel).


 The 5.56mm/.223 Rem. caliber 16" barrel is chrome lined in both bore and chamber for long wear life and ease of maintenance. For control of muzzle flash and muzzle rise in rapid fire, a “birdcage” type suppressor is factory installed. A mil. spec. manganese phosphate outer coating insures protection against corrosion or rust on the barrel and all critical steel parts of the weapon. 

Forged, lightweight 7075T6 aircraft quality aluminum receivers are designed for simplicity of maintenance and reliability of operation and they incorporate all M16A2 design improvements including cartridge case deflector, bolt catch assembly and raised ribs for protection against accidental magazine release. A six position telescoping buttstock offers light weight, carrying ease and quick handling. 

The telestock, pistol grip and two piece handguards are all molded of strong black thermoset composite material. The handguards are internally shielded against barrel heat build-up. The dual aperture M16A2 rear sight system on these carbines offer both windage and elevation adjustment calibrated in meters. 

The A3 Type Patrolman’s Carbine includes a Removable Carry Handle - adjustment range is from from 300 to 600 meters (1/2 M.o.A. elevation and 1/2 M.o.A. windage).

Once the Carry Handle is removed, a wide variety of scopes, red dot or holographic sights, or night vision equipment may be mounted on the Upper Receiver’s integral Picatinny rail. Iron sight zero is completely repeatable when the handle is reattached by means of its knurled knobs. 

The Bushmaster A2/A3 Type Patrolman’s Carbines are shipped complete with 30 round magazine, safety and operational manual, and carry sling.
